{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-18",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_18_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Fall Guy",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 8,
  "page_start_sec": 260.88,
  "page_end_sec": 501.16,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.553,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 260.88,
      "end": 263.26,
      "text": "His dark eyes had the surface-shine of lacquer."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.06,
      "end": 266.14,
      "text": "They shifted their focus warily from Spade's"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.26,
      "end": 268.78,
      "text": "face to Gutman's, from Gutman's to Spade's."
    },
    {
      "start": 269.14,
      "end": 270.22,
      "text": "Gutman repeated,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 270.58,
      "end": 271.2,
      "text": "well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.28,
      "end": 271.54,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.7,
      "end": 272.42,
      "text": "as to that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 273.02,
      "end": 273.68,
      "text": "and took a white"
    },
    {
      "start": 273.76,
      "end": 274.86,
      "text": "envelope from his pocket."
    },
    {
      "start": 275.22,
      "end": 280.4,
      "text": "Ten eyes—the boy's now only half obscured by his lashes—looked at the envelope."
    },
    {
      "start": 281.568,
      "end": 283.72,
      "text": "Turning the envelope over in his swollen hands,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 283.98,
      "end": 286.36,
      "text": "Gutman studied for a moment its blank white"
    },
    {
      "start": 286.46,
      "end": 287.96,
      "text": "front and then its back,"
    },
    {
      "start": 288.06,
      "end": 288.92,
      "text": "unsealed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 289.22,
      "end": 290.2,
      "text": "with the flap tucked in."
    },
    {
      "start": 290.46,
      "end": 291.96,
      "text": "He raised his head,"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.1,
      "end": 293.3,
      "text": "smiled amiably,"
    },
    {
      "start": 293.56,
      "end": 295.76,
      "text": "and scaled the envelope at Spade's lap."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.1,
      "end": 297.14,
      "text": "The envelope,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 297.32,
      "end": 298.0,
      "text": "though not bulky,"
    },
    {
      "start": 298.2,
      "end": 299.0,
      "text": "was heavy enough"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.0,
      "end": 299.64,
      "text": "to fly true."
    },
    {
      "start": 300.42,
      "end": 302.04,
      "text": "It struck the lower part of Spade's"
    },
    {
      "start": 302.04,
      "end": 303.78,
      "text": "chest and dropped down on his thighs."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.74,
      "end": 305.02,
      "text": "He picked"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.02,
      "end": 307.22,
      "text": "it up deliberately and opened it deliberately,"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.52,
      "end": 308.6,
      "text": "using both hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 308.84,
      "end": 311.0,
      "text": "having taken his left arm from"
    },
    {
      "start": 311.1,
      "end": 311.86,
      "text": "around the girl."
    },
    {
      "start": 312.9,
      "end": 315.16,
      "text": "The contents of the envelope were thousand-dollar bills,"
    },
    {
      "start": 315.38,
      "end": 316.82,
      "text": "smooth and stiff and new."
    },
    {
      "start": 317.824,
      "end": 319.3,
      "text": "Spade took them out and counted them."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.92,
      "end": 320.72,
      "text": "There were ten of them."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.568,
      "end": 322.26,
      "text": "Spade looked up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 322.28,
      "end": 322.52,
      "text": "smiling."
    },
    {
      "start": 323.44,
      "end": 324.08,
      "text": "He said mildly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.42,
      "end": 327.14,
      "text": "We were talking about more money than this."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.88,
      "end": 328.28,
      "text": "Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 328.34,
      "end": 328.54,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.56,
      "end": 328.98,
      "text": "we were,"
    },
    {
      "start": 329.1,
      "end": 329.72,
      "text": "Gutman agreed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 330.42,
      "end": 331.54,
      "text": "but we were talking then."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.6,
      "end": 333.88,
      "text": "This is actual money,"
    },
    {
      "start": 334.88,
      "end": 336.36,
      "text": "genuine coin of the realm,"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.46,
      "end": 336.72,
      "text": "sir."
    },
    {
      "start": 337.54,
      "end": 338.46,
      "text": "With a dollar of this,"
    },
    {
      "start": 338.46,
      "end": 340.92,
      "text": "you can buy more than with ten dollars of talk."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.792,
      "end": 343.3,
      "text": "Silent laughter shook his bulbs."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.42,
      "end": 345.5,
      "text": "When their commotion stopped,"
    },
    {
      "start": 345.82,
      "end": 347.0,
      "text": "he said more seriously,"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.82,
      "end": 349.09,
      "text": "yet not altogether seriously."
    },
    {
      "start": 350.14,
      "end": 352.06,
      "text": "There are more of us to be taken care of now."
    },
    {
      "start": 352.38,
      "end": 356.44,
      "text": "He moved his twinkling eyes and his fat head to indicate Cairo."
    },
    {
      "start": 357.3,
      "end": 357.66,
      "text": "And,"
    },
    {
      "start": 357.66,
      "end": 358.16,
      "text": "well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.18,
      "end": 358.5,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.7,
      "end": 359.68,
      "text": "in short,"
    },
    {
      "start": 359.8,
      "end": 361.54,
      "text": "the situation has changed."
    },
    {
      "start": 362.54,
      "end": 363.3,
      "text": "While Gutman talked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 363.58,
      "end": 366.52,
      "text": "Spade had tapped the edges of the ten bills into alignment"
    },
    {
      "start": 366.74,
      "end": 368.28,
      "text": "and returned them to their envelope,"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.6,
      "end": 370.2,
      "text": "tucking the flap in over them."
    },
    {
      "start": 370.9,
      "end": 371.24,
      "text": "Now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 371.24,
      "end": 372.38,
      "text": "with forearms on knees,"
    },
    {
      "start": 372.58,
      "end": 373.64,
      "text": "he sat hunched forward,"
    },
    {
      "start": 374.304,
      "end": 376.46,
      "text": "dangling the envelope from a corner held lightly"
    },
    {
      "start": 376.46,
      "end": 378.74,
      "text": "by finger and thumb down between his legs."
    },
    {
      "start": 379.6,
      "end": 381.18,
      "text": "His reply to the fat man was careless."
    },
    {
      "start": 381.38,
      "end": 381.6,
      "text": "Sure,"
    },
    {
      "start": 382.94,
      "end": 383.68,
      "text": "you're together now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 384.2,
      "end": 385.26,
      "text": "but I've got the falcon."
    },
    {
      "start": 386.28,
      "end": 387.12,
      "text": "Joel Cairo spoke.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 388.32,
      "end": 389.38,
      "text": "Ugly hands grasping"
    },
    {
      "start": 389.38,
      "end": 390.48,
      "text": "the arms of his chair,"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.62,
      "end": 394.24,
      "text": "he leaned forward and said primly in his high-pitched thin voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.88,
      "end": 397.78,
      "text": "I shouldn't think it would be necessary to remind you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 397.86,
      "end": 398.06,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.18,
      "end": 398.48,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.7,
      "end": 400.08,
      "text": "that though you may have the"
    },
    {
      "start": 400.26,
      "end": 400.48,
      "text": "falcon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 400.68,
      "end": 402.6,
      "text": "yet we certainly have you."
    },
    {
      "start": 403.616,
      "end": 404.38,
      "text": "Spade grinned.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 405.472,
      "end": 407.3,
      "text": "I'm trying to not let that worry me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 407.42,
      "end": 407.82,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 408.06,
      "end": 409.5,
      "text": "He sat up straight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 410.3,
      "end": 412.4,
      "text": "put the envelope aside—on the sofa—"
    },
    {
      "start": 412.52,
      "end": 413.68,
      "text": "and addressed Gutman."
    },
    {
      "start": 414.76,
      "end": 416.1,
      "text": "We'll come back to the money later."
    },
    {
      "start": 416.896,
      "end": 419.06,
      "text": "There's another thing that's got to be taken care of first."
    },
    {
      "start": 419.84,
      "end": 421.06,
      "text": "We've got to have a fall-guy."
    },
    {
      "start": 422.08,
      "end": 423.72,
      "text": "The fat man frowned without comprehension,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 424.32,
      "end": 425.3,
      "text": "but before he could speak,"
    },
    {
      "start": 425.38,
      "end": 426.28,
      "text": "Spade was explaining."
    },
    {
      "start": 427.3,
      "end": 428.74,
      "text": "The police have got to have a victim,"
    },
    {
      "start": 428.9,
      "end": 431.26,
      "text": "somebody they can stick for those three murders."
    },
    {
      "start": 431.84,
      "end": 431.98,
      "text": "We,"
    },
    {
      "start": 432.44,
      "end": 434.26,
      "text": "Cairo, speaking in a brittle excited voice, interrupted Spade.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 434.32,
      "end": 435.04,
      "text": "\"Two—only two—murders, Mr. Spade. Thursby undoubtedly killed your partner.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 435.12,
      "end": 435.98,
      "text": "\"All right, two,\" Spade growled."
    },
    {
      "start": 436.62,
      "end": 438.44,
      "text": "\"What difference does that make? The point is we've got to feed the police some—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 450.06,
      "end": 451.14,
      "text": "Now Gutman broke in, smiling confidently, talking with good-natured assurance:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 451.26,
      "end": 454.02,
      "text": "\"Well, sir, from what we've seen and heard of you I don't think we'll have to bother ourselves about that."
    },
    {
      "start": 454.02,
      "end": 457.22,
      "text": "We can leave the handling of the police to you, all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 457.28,
      "end": 460.62,
      "text": "You won't need any of our inexpert help.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 467.8,
      "end": 468.8,
      "text": "If that's what you think,"
    },
    {
      "start": 469.26,
      "end": 469.64,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 469.84,
      "end": 471.7,
      "text": "you haven't seen or heard enough."
    },
    {
      "start": 472.68,
      "end": 473.02,
      "text": "\"Now come, Mr. Spade.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 473.18,
      "end": 473.32,
      "text": "You can't expect us to believe at this late date that you are the least bit afraid of the police,"
    },
    {
      "start": 473.52,
      "end": 473.98,
      "text": "or that you are not quite able to handle—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 482.528,
      "end": 484.44,
      "text": "Spade snorted with throat and nose.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 485.26,
      "end": 485.9,
      "text": "He bent forward,"
    },
    {
      "start": 486.06,
      "end": 487.7,
      "text": "resting forearms on knees again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 488.16,
      "end": 489.8,
      "text": "and interrupted Gutman irritably:"
    },
    {
      "start": 490.41,
      "end": 492.36,
      "text": "\"I'm not a damned bit afraid of them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 492.72,
      "end": 494.18,
      "text": "and I know how to handle them."
    },
    {
      "start": 494.752,
      "end": 496.14,
      "text": "That's what I'm trying to tell you."
    },
    {
      "start": 496.9,
      "end": 498.96,
      "text": "The way to handle them is to toss them a victim,"
    },
    {
      "start": 499.52,
      "end": 501.16,
      "text": "somebody they can hang the works on.\""
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}